The face of poverty is black. The face of inequality is black. The face of hunger is black. The face of crime is black. The face of slavery is black. The face of immigrants is black. The face of oppression is black. The face of illiteracy is black. The face of disease is black. The face of wars is black. The face of child and women abuse is black. Is it because the Bible says God chose Israel and its people to be his nation? Nonu Kekana Evaton, Vaal Triangle